  "instructions": [
    "In a large donabe, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the katsuramuki-cut zucchini and carrots, cooking for 5 minutes or until tender.",
    "Add the cornmeal and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the water, salt, and black pepper, stirring to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Stir in the lemon juice and harissa.",
    "Garnish with fresh parsley and cilantro before serving.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!",
    "Let the tagine rest for 5 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together."
